The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Sept. 28: Indias external debt rose 5.6 per cent to $165.4 billion for the quarter ended June 2007 as domestic companies increased overseas borrowings and the local currency strengthened against the greenback. Of the $8.7-billion increase from the March-end figure, a $1.2 billion rise in external debt was on account of valuation effects. This reflected depreciation of the dollar against other major international currencies. 

 Mumbai, Sept. 28: A subsidiary of Reliance Energy (REL) may be looking at an option of an initial public offering of up to $3 billion as part of resource mobilisation for setting up power plants, according to some international news reports that could not be confirmed from Reliance Energy officials. 

 Mumbai, Sept. 28: The board of Arvind Mills has cleared a plan to issue 5.06 crore equity warrants to promoters, which will entitle them to one share per warrant on conversion. The warrants are convertible into equity shares within a period of 18 months in one or more tranches at a price of Rs 52 per share.

 New Delhi, Sept. 28: The government plans to set up a petroleum, chemical and petrochemical investment region (PCPIR) by January 2008 and is in the process of scrutinising proposals from Andhra Pradesh, Gujarat and Karnataka governments.

 New Delhi, Sept. 28: Del Monte Pacific, the US-based food and beverage company, has picked up a 40 per cent stake in Bharti Enterprises-promoted farm venture Fieldfresh. Industry sources said the deal is in the range of Rs 350 crore to Rs 400 crore.

 Mumbai, Sept. 28: United Breweries will raise Rs 425 crore through issue of equity shares on rights basis to existing shareholders. Terms will be finalised by a committee of directors.

 Mumbai, Sept. 28: ICICI Bank has raised $2 billion from a fixed rate note through its Bahrain branch for general corporate purpose.




